column1: I am a down-to-earth person, who believes in the basic good values of life i.e, God fearing, respect for others and working hard to do better in life. In this complex world of busy schedules and fast life, there is always a moment to do prayer daily and do my part in charitable work that can make a difference in other peoples' lives. Overall, I believe I am a giving person without seeking much in return. I see my life as a beautiful collection of things that the Almighty gave me out of my good fortune and I am so glad to live this blessed life. I enjoy every moment of it and want to share it with that Special Someone. I respect and regard the views of others. I especially get along very well with my elders. In my daily profession of being a doctor, I have the opportunity to treat so many diverse people with various illnesses. Also, I do teaching in my office during which medical students come for their core rotation in Medicine. This gives me tremendous satisfaction to see that some of my students go on to become great doctors with some of the principles that I taught them while they were rotating with me. column1: My name is Raam Balram. I am a South African of Indian descent. My grandfather arrived in South Africa from India in 1895. My father has deceased. I have a mom who can be classified as the best in the world. I, fortunately, have my mother's good qualities. I am kind, friendly and have very sober habits. I love life. I like to be with nature and animals. I love literature and hence my desire to read. I feel that I can love. I can look after my responsibilities. I care a lot about family values and traditions. We, in South Africa, believe in mixing traditions. The East fuses with the West. Being in Johannesburg, means that we do compromise on the Eastern traditions. However, I visit my mom in Durban for doses of tradition. I am an undergraduate and a postgraduate. No problems with academic achievements. I am about 5 feet 8 inches in height. I used to adorn a beard . I am clean shaven now. I am a part time lecturer at an international college in Braamfontein, Johannesburg. I like to be neatly turned out all times. I have my own car. Public transport in Johannesburg is good. We have the metro buses, Ria - Vaya Buses, cabs and taxis and the Gautrain. My favorite colors are the lighter shades of blue and green. Always believe that the right to speak is preceded by a duty to listen. Respect is earned.,"I hope that you are the lady that I am looking for. Please be your normal self when making a judgement. Tick the boxes as you read what follows. Must be a simple person. Should not have children. Between ages group of between 40 to 48 and single. Must be well mannered. Easy to communicate to. Should have a sense of humor. Must ideally be independent in terms of career and financial care. Must be willing to travel in South Africa. my home is in Johannesburg. this is in Gauteng Province and about 7,000 feet above sea level. no humidity in this part of the world, must be willing to share and make joint decisions, i have no issues if person indulges in meat, i come from a big family, should not be technologically challenged, should be able to drive on her own. Must not be challenged by body mass. Should be a good home maker but balanced with career inspirations, no difficulties with my partner pursuing a career and academic pursuits. Should believe in our Creator. Restrain tempers. Its good to be a listener than a speaker in some instances. Right to speak is preceded by duty to listen, keen to communicate in English (80%). Must be responsible & versatile : capable of accepting change . ","I live in my own house in Observatory, Johannesburg, Gauteng Province, South Africa. My future wife will live with me at this address. We will visit my family in Verulam, Durban, Kwa Zulu Natal monthly. I have my mom and my 2 sister in laws. column1: I am a good looking well established professional for last 20 years. I have a 15 year old son from last marriage who stays with my former wife. If someone is leaving her country and loved ones behind for me, I will make damn sure that she is happy and very well taken care of. I am very respectful for woman, their thoughts, their needs, and their ambitions. Woman is my other half, my life is not complete if you are not their. Companionship is mutual respect, love, affection, holding hands and walking together, caring, longing, supporting, and lot of friendship. Live and let live. Live your today, you get one chance to make it happen, love, laugh and make it happen. You will not get this life again. So give, enjoy and let go. Give it to your wife, give it to your son, love your family. Make friends, love your wife, live life do not let it go. No matter how much you agree or disagree, how much you argue, at the end of the day. column1:
Simplicity is the one of the best qualities in people. I admire this in people and I am very proud to say that I possess the same quality. According to me, it is the most wonderful thing. People who are simple are respected a lot by people. 
Being simple is like an asset to me. Many people around me respect me because of that. I am in the good books of people whom I like because of this. However, sometimes I suffer because of this habit of mine. People take advantage of me at times. 
I am into Government Service and I am Senior Supervisor in a PSU. I am very happy with my profession and I am satisfied with the act that I have professional stability. I want to stick to the same field and achieve the maximum growth in it. 
I have done a Diploma in Electrical Engineering from MEI Polytechnic, Bangalore. I was always a very sincere person, not only in student life but while I was working too. 

When I have some days off from work, I pack my bags and go out for travelling with my family or with my friends.,"I prefer a girl who is from Karnataka or Bangalore. This is because I live in Bangalore and I want the girl to be from nearby. This way she will not have much trouble in adjusting with the place. She can also visit her parents whenever she feels like without travelling much.

I would like to marry a homemaker. This is because I would like her to take care of the family and household. I am sure she will seek a lot of respect and love from me if she is an efficient homemaker. This is very important in a relationship.
I donAa?a?t have many people in my family but four sisters. I hope she is successful in carrying out a good and healthy relationship with them. They all will adore her a lot if she is like that.

She needs to be very caring and loving. This will not only help her in seeking love and respect from me but my family too. They will adore her if she is affectionate to them. Her loving nature can avoid many problems and quarrels that families have these days.

The girl I get married to needs to be very adjustable. If she adjusts in my family sooner she will get a lot of love and care from my family members. I am sure she will enjoy it and give them the same love back.

She will have a wonderful married life if she is what I expect her to be.",I have lost both my parents and now that I do not have them I miss them a lot. I have four sisters and they all are very close to me. I have always been there for them and I am sure I will be there for them in future too. ,18 to 18,18 Apr 1955,07:25:00,India,Bangalore,Slim,Doesn't Matter,,Others,,,,Fair ,Fair,Self,Other Diploma,"58 yrs, 5ft 7in,

It is very difficult to describe oneself in a truthful manner. However, let me try to do the same. I am a simple person having the weakness to be caring, kindhearted, down to earth, passionate, jovial on majority of occasions, which are not liked by many in this materialistic world. Sometimes, I am also workholic. I had the weakness to learn which resulted in obtaining Doctorate in French Language from J.N.U., New Delhi and thereafter LLB from Delhi University. I had the weakness to write thereby resulting in expressing my points of view of varied subjects, though my view differ with majority views. My parents are no more- mother died in 1974 when I was 13 years old and Father died in 1982 when I was 21years old. God never blessed me with any sister. I had one elder brother, who had also died in 2005 leaving behind his wife, three young and handsome sons and a beautiful daughter, who have done graduation and post graduation. My last marriage lead to mutual divorce in the Court. I had thought to pass the remaining life alone, but feel need of a companion, so all this search. I am a cosmopolitan and do not believe in differentia on caste, creed, religion etc. for which I feel my companion to be independent in her endeavour. column1: Hi, I am a smart, tall guy and my personality belies my age. Basically, a management professional by qualification and a creative director out of sheer passion to tell a visual story. column1: Life is A Celebration Enjoy!!!! You Live Only Once!! I believe in the dictum - love to live, live to love. Enthusiasm is the best protection in any situation. Wholeheartedness is contagious, so give yourself, if you wish to get others. It is your life, just imagine the possibilities! I am looking for a partner who can celebrate the joy called 'life' with me. I want tons of laughter, loads of peace and a world of giving and sharing. Although should say that was an avid reader, non fiction, philosophy, biographies, adventures real stuff of course always aroused my literary instincts slowed down a little bit time does not permit hoping to catch up on the reading. column1: Presently working as ASST. GENERAL MANAGER (MM); i.e.middle Management level, in a Steel Sector company, a Central Govt PSU. I am working in this organization for over 25yrs by now and drawing monthly salary above Rs 49000/- per month (gross) +perks. My job is non-transferable type and I live in the integrated company township well equipped with all facilities required for a decent living. I am Hindu/Jat (Age: 48 yrs), looks much younger & energetic, with family roots in Delhi & Haryana (Gothra self - sangwan & motherA?s -malik). I am smart, handsome with medium built & fair complexion. I am a simple living person, vegetarian, non-smoker, and teetotaler with no vice of any kind and fully devoted to the family and its welfare. I am practical, karmyogi, and down to earth person. I have enjoyed 16 yrs of marital life with no history of any family discord and blessed with two children (daughter 14 yrs & son 9 yrs). However, divorce that was sought by her has been granted by Supreme Court of India in AugA?06 and case for custody of minor children presently with her and under contest, is going on in High court. I continue to lead a happy and peaceful life with the present settled job in this beautiful port city of Visakhapatnam and fully committed towards my duty and responsibility towards my children in all possible ways till they become independent and embark on some career. I was born & all along brought-up in Delhi where my parents resided for nearly 45 years. My both sisters are married and settled abroad for over 20 yrs, i.e, in Riyadh (Saudi Arabia) & Seoul (S.Korea). My both brother-in-laws are doctors and settled well in good positions in the above countries. My only brother, elder to me, works for Delhi State Govt. and resides in New Delhi-110001 for over 25 years with his family. My Father who died 6 yrs back was an officer and retired from central govt. job and my mother is simple house-wife. She keeps visiting me but mostly stays at Delhi especially when my sisters visit India from abroad. I thus seek, a matrimonial alliance from educated -- unmarried/widow /divorcee lady of age group 35-43yrs without any issues or physical handicap belonging to good & respected Hindu North Indian family. To be frank, I am interested in an alliance partner who will prefer to lead a peaceful homely life with me in full dignity & honour. If someone harbors any special personal objectives or career goals in life at this middle age (except interest in a teaching job locally), it may not be possible in my place of job/stay. column1: I was born in Bangalore & brought up & educated in Mumbai. Very fair, tall, handsome & looking much younger. I am simple & straight-forward in nature; sincere towards everything in life & hardworking person with a religious bent of mind, valuing customs & traditions, but with a modern, practical outlook. I am staying seperately & alone due to nuclear-family compulsions. On advice of friends & relatives, I started to search for a suitable life-partner now only afresh. Well qualified, served a nationalised & international bank for 25 years; 10 years as an OFFICER, before opting for VRS, now satisfactorily employed in the private sector. I possess own flat in Mumbai & another one in its distant suburbs. Basically we are South Indian Brahmins hailing originally from Thanjavur. Since there is no seperate language categorization for my mother tongue while registering the profile, I wanted to mention mother tongue in this manner: ' Kannada / Tamil.' I have entered Kannada as my mother tongue since only one language can be mentioned; but some language has to be mentioned. I could have equally entered Tamil too as my mother tongue. There is no arrangement to mention both Kannada & Tamil as my mother tongue. We factually speak Thanjavur Marathi at home, which is different from the usual Marathi spoken in Maharashtra. But having been brought up in Mumbai since birth, I have studied the regional language Marathi & know to read & speak. Thanjavur Marathi is a mixture of Sanskrit, Old Marathi, Kannada & Tamil words. Hence I know both the languages Kannada & Tamil & can understand little Malayalam & Telugu as well. People from our community are miniscule in number. It is common in our community to make matrimonial alliances with Kannada & Tamil (Iyer / Iyengar) speaking Brahmins, & Kannada / Tamil (Iyer / Iyengar) speaking Brahmins also do not hesitate to give their sons or daughters in marriage with our community, so much so that some of our relatives are speaking Kannada / Tamil at home as their mother tongue because we share a common religion, culture, tradition, customs & practices as South Indian Brahmins with regard to celebration of festivals or conducting thread ceremony or marriage ceremony etc. My hobbies include reading books, magazines & newspapers, listening to Carnatic Classical Vocal as well as Carnatic music & also other kinds of songs and music in different regional languages including Hindi, English, learning languages, visiting places of tourist & religious interest, yoga, pranayama & meditation etc. I have completed several Yoga & Pranayama Courses. I love small chidren, nature, flora & fauna. I am also a Shri Krishna [Gaudia Mutt & ISKCON], Swamy Ayyappan, Shirdi Sai Baba, Satya Sai Baba & Avadhoot Baba Shivanand devotee, presently attending their respective satsangs, but willing to change as per circumstances after marriage. I have also done The Art Of Living Course & attending Veda & Swami Chinmayananda Study Group Vedanta Classes in spare time. As judged by others, I am a person of clean habits, having no vices & encumbrances at all. In short, Responsible, Respectful, Caring & Sharing, Loving, Family oriented person. Love to travel. Hailing from a good family background. I only aspire for mutual love, affection, caring & to settle down once again with peace & happiness in life. Thank you very much for your kind interest & enormous patience in reading this profile till the end & best wishes to you for finding a suitable life-partner.,"A life-partner should be any BRAHMIN, sub-caste no bar & should profess pure vegetarianism. Unmarried profiles are most welcome. Widow & Divorcee profiles without children & with children upto three years of age also equally welcome. ","My family consists of only younger brother, who is employed in a nationalized bank & his family who are decently settled separately. I have no sisters. My parents have expired. I am staying all alone in my father's own house. column1: My nature is that of a simple and decent person who is understanding and has experience of life. I am a very dedicated person and very sincere about my work. I have deep interest in investing money in quality shares & pursue it as a hobby for wealth creation. column1: I am an independent person with a strong interest in languages, literature, experimental movies, music of all sorts( Classical to some country). I am not a templegoer but deeply spiritual and find spiritual and useful messages in all religious thoughts. I read Gita and Bible with equal reverance. Anthropology and science fascinates me and art moves my soul. I like to write and read. Mostly fiction and philosophical treaties. I am a conversationalist with passion to listen a good discourse on just about any subject. Outdoors is my life. I do not visit Malls and shopping center for pleasure. like challenges in life and I will seek them as long as I can perform. I manage three companies as a CEO and that is not so much important as the other things I wrote here. Research in human endeavors such as literature, arts and science is my primary interest. I like nature therefore being in garden admiring flowers, plants and dipping in flowing brooks are my favorite things. I love western dancing and enjoy Indian Classical dances and music immensely. I like sipping wine while reading poetry and go for trekking in the mountains of Colorado or Mesa in the New Mexico desert when I can. I am not a Hollywood/Bollywood fan and watch selective experimental movies; mainly non-American international low budget movies. I enjoy watching Sports (Cricket and American Football). I like cooking and experiment with foods. My favorite eating-places are Japanese Sushi Bars, Ethiopian, French and Vietnamese. I have profound respect for compassionate and kind people. Lastly, I wish to remember Landor's stanza when I am on the verge of leaving this world: " I strove with none, None was worth my strife. I loved nature; next to nature Art. I warmed my both hands on fire of life. It sinks and I am ready to depart.","I seek only companionship of that special one who will enlighten me, cherish my being and allow me to discover her so to know her and love her as if we both are just stepping out of our youth. Education and self sufficiency is important because I will want to have relationship which Gibran described as AA?A?two shores of an ocean where the oceanic waves of love and delightful coexistence will connect us, wash us and enrich us with one grain of sand given or taken away from us.AA?A? Looks are important but the news media defined beauty is not. Looks reflect beauty of inner thoughts; those spring up without reasons and purpose when one is alone and contemplative like WordsworthAA?A?s Daffodils. Healthy and willing to go trekking with me in the beautiful mountains and bicycling through the forest trails will add romance to our lives, which is beyond the imagination of any bedroom lover. I am all yours if this fits into your needs. I ideal partner must be an organized person, matured by life experiences, she should be a professional open for enrichment through knowledge and ideals. I am not looking for a slave in the kitchen or in bedroom. Her love for me should be grown by discovering my personality and qualities not by compulssion or obligations. I seek a compassionate soul, with a positve attitude, an advisor and a friend. There are no children to raise so she must look at life as the Almighties blessings for enjoying the good things this life offers. I hope you are out there.",,,25 Jul 1942,00:04:00,United States of America,Amravati,Athletic,,,,,,,Fair ,,Self,Masters,"71 yrs, 5ft 6in,

column1: This is Gautam from Assam famous for its one horned Rhinos and Assam tea . I am intelligent, simple, loving, caring, sensitive, emotional, have a good sense of humor, God fearing and posses pleasing personality. I like to go for long drives and enjoy listening to good music. Cooking and gardening are my hobies. I play tennis and badminton . I also like to go for fishing. I also like to read books. I enjoy dancing and partying. Presently I am separated and have one son who is not living with me. Would describe myself as confident, calm, friendly, caring, honest, reliable, genuine, cheeky, playful . I have a great sense of humour and am looking for same in a partner. I am also emotionally and financially secure. I believe in chemistry. Either two people meet and feel a connection or they don't. Two perfectly nice, attractive people may not necessarily be attracted to each other. If there is no chemistry you cannot force it to be there. I am a loving, kind, and generous person. I believe that two people in a relationship are each, at least partially, responsible for the other's happiness. I say what I mean and mean what I say. I don't make promises I do not intend to keep. I don't believe in mind games or power struggles or manipulation or control. These things are toxic to a relationships. I want someone who will be my best friend, and I will be her. Someone to laugh and be silly with and who will be there for me, as I would for her, if I cry. Someone who will genuinely care about my well being and does not always put her own needs and concerns first. P. S. Fair is Fair - I will not respond to anyone who does not include her photo! column1: My father was a Air Force officer and mother a home maker, we are a very respectable and cultured family from Patna Bihar. I had four brothers and one sister, I am the youngest in the family. in 1980 my parents moved to kolkata.Two of my brothers, one a doctor in UK and another a businessman in Australia have died, my sister is a widow and she lives with her younger son in their own flat in the same city as me(Kolkata)I was married for 35 years and now a divorce. I have two beautiful daughters who are both married and well settled in USA.I also have two grand daughters, thatA?s as far as my family life goes I am living alone in India, in the state of West Bengal, in the capitol city of Kolkata, that is south Kolkata.I speak and write English, Bengali and Hindi, aged about 59 years, 6ft 1 in tall, weighing about 115 Kg fair, in good. Live in my own flat and my source of earning is my six figure pension. I have traveled widely around the country and round the world. I am basically an engineer with an MBA degree. Love sports, music, dancing, outing and getting to know people, generally having lot and lots of fun. I am a straight forward, honest and sincere man. I hate negative people, since I am a very positive thing and never give up easily. When required I use my car but that is very seldom, since coming to kolkata I have not met many people of my choice and values, hence the need to go out is seldom. I see movies on my TV, since I do not like to go out alone, usually like comedies in Hindi and English, since Bengali has very little comedy, the last Bengali comedy I saw wasA? dada kirthiA?the English serial Friends, Hindi I like watching movies like hera pheri, golmaal, etc, etc.I do not like watching serious movies since in real live we already are very serious. My interest lies in meeting like minded people for chatting, parting and generally having fun, if during these inter action I meet someone of my liking and she also likes me I am willing to discuss permanent settlement.A? God willingA?, I love soul music basically in Hindi and Bengali rabindra sangeet, English blues, but since coming to kolkata I have hardly heard English songs. I used to love listing to Clive Richards, Elvis, Engle Burt, martin, etc. I love to eat out, especially around Park Street, but do not like to go out alone so I fulfill my desires by ordering good food from restaurants around south kolkata whenever I like. I just love good non-vegetarian Indian food and have no taste for foreign foodes, like Italian, Mexican, Spanish, japanease or Chinese. I am looking for similar minded female friends.,"She should be honest,caring from a respectable family and willing to enjoy life to it's full,fun loving liberal thinking,one who likes music,travelling,dessing,partying and is willing to share everthing with me with no with holds",,40 to 50,11 Nov 1953,,India,,Average,,,Brahmin - Bengali,,Kolkata,,Doesn't Matter,,Self,BE B.Tech (Engineering),"60 yrs, 6ft 1in,

column1: I was born in Bangalore, in the year 1962. In the year 1964-65 my family shifted to Delhi and since than we have been staying here. I am sensitive, shy, sincere, straightforward and hardworking person. Very found of Music. I have learnt Hindustani Classical Music till Madhyama II year (Hawain Guitar) from Gandharva Mahavidhyala, Delhi and capable of playing various kinds of musical Instruments. I take private Tutions for Guitar, Keyboard etc. I am also associated with an Orchestra group. Academically I could not excel much on account of certain unavoidable situations and circumstances, which prevailed in the family due to various factors and reasons. (Details will telll you later). Unfortunately during such juncture, it was only my studies that were mostly affected, in comparison to my siblings; as such the impact of the losses & damages caused with respect to my studies initially, continued and affected in my further education as well. Thus, I could not pursue my studies after matriculation. Moreover due to existence of economical uncertainty in the family because of father being jobless, I along with other siblings had to take up different jobs at an early and had to support the family to minimize the financial crisis that had been prevailing during those difficult and unforgettable days. Thereafter gradually things got improved & stabilized and one after the other all my brother and sisters got married except myself. Currently I am working as Asstt. Administrative Officer in a Private Limited company and I am associated with this company since last 22 years. Taking into consideration my childhood memories, experience and my family's sufferings etc. initially I was determined never to get married. Now with the passage of time, recently I have experienced isolaltion & loneliness, finding nobody with whom I could share my sorrows and grievances. Thus, I am now in search for a suitable partner/companion with whom I wish to spend rest of the life peacefully & happily. Although my destiny did not allow me to do well academically, however it is my sincere wish and dream that at least my spouse to be well qualified and preferably working and self-dependent. My famaily consists of father who is a freedom fighter, scholar, a man of high principles, honest and straiaghtforward person. He had spent and devoted most of his time on social and other similar activities rather then giving priority and first preference to discharge his duties & responsibilities towards his own family. Mother is a housewife and she is the backbone of our family. Both are staying with me. Elder brother is associated with Delhi Science Form, his spouse is a Proffessor & head of History department in a reputed College in Delhi University (North campus) and both are staying in their staff quarters in University campus. Out of three sisters elder one is settled in Bangalore working in Indian Airlines. Second one married to a French and settled in France, she was working as Air Hostess with Royal Jordanian Airlines. Youngest one very loving and affectionate is also settled in Delhi. If interested and ready to accept me as I am irrespective of my qualification and mere source of income, may contact me for further details. With best wishes.,"To be honest,sincere,affectionate,loving,adjustable,coopeative, straightforward. She should be working.","Father is a Freedom Fighter now retired. Mother is a House Wife. Brother is associated with Delhi Science Form. His wife is Head of department (History) Miranda College, Delhi University. Elder Sister is married and settled in Banglore working with Indian Airlines. Second sister is married to a French and now settled in France. Youngest sister is also married and leaving in Delhi.",29 to 44,10 Jun 1962,,India,Bangalore,Slim,Doesn't Matter,,,,Delhi,,Dark ,Doesn't Matter,Self,10th,"51 yrs, 5ft 9in,

Marriage happens only once. That is what I personally believe in. When both the players have deep respect for the marriage institute, play the game with fare intention; solemnly follow set of rules without looking beyond each other. When you learn to live harmoniously with your better half, you grow, mingle and dissolve together evolving into a homogeneous entity forming a perfect concoction  called AA?A?soulmatesAA?A?. My late wife was a charismatic, beautiful, sensible and an intelligent lady whom I searched in the crowd after a great toil. But a personal tragedy took her away in the prime of her life.
Life has to go on and it is only one life you are endowed with of which you are conscious of. The concept of HOME is incomplete without a woman and I believe that a woman is an axis around which the entire house revolves and the lives of its occupants are woven. 

On a positive note, a second chance make you more sensitive towards life and one really learns that all those small and seemingly insignificant moments of life which passed unnoticed/overlooked were of tremendous importance when one pauses, stands and stares and absorbs them with a lovely smile. Your whole perspective of life gets a complete overhaul. 

Relationships are always to be worked out and need time to mature.

Self Assessment:

Describing me myself is not that important. When it comes to describe oneself it is a tremendous task. One can choose so many catchy adjectives for self description. But all the words are likely to loose their meaning and sheen when you view them with your own perspective. How can I be self judgmental?

I am a typical Scorpio and thanks to Linda GoodmanAA?A?s Star Signs for elaborately describing my personal traits and deep routed secrets. A straight-forward and forthright person, I am physically pleasant, mentally strong, emotionally delicate (idiot) and spiritually evolved. 

I have a romantic passion for everything that I undertake. Deeply interested in all Fine Art fields. I occasionally write poems and delve in paintings. Music uplifts my soul and gives fluidity to my emotions.

I like reading literature; preferably Classics. That is a gift my wife gave to me. Thomas Hardy is my favorite.

I love photography and am an ardent reader of Indian history which inspires me for embarking upon journeys to off track places. 

I am deeply in love with the Himalayas and perfectly tuned with nature. Cooking is a sort of meditation for me. Keeping my home spick & span is my pastime.

My energy level being high, I always keep myself indulged in some or the other creative activity and can not sit still.

I have passion for rain and canAA?A?t resist the temptation of walking in rain. I feel like melting in rain.
I have been practicing Yoga for the past 30 years. I love to go for trekking and undertake walks for miles.

I have no any ambition; I am not in race for money and am fully contended. I am thankful to the God for whatever He has given to me. I am not a kind of person who keeps on going to temples for fulfillment of his desires since I have almost none. I donAA?A?t follow any set path of praying or indulging in any sort of rituals. I am like a bird set to fly in infinite space.,"I donA?t want a Companion for cooking food and doing other household errands for me. We are skillful in home management. I believe in complete liberation of a woman and freedom of choices in every sphere of life. I understand that each individual need space to grow and blossom and has his on individual self that need not to be encroached upon by any other member.

I want a companion who can walk in rain and chase butterflies with me. Listen music with me and can sit silently for hours A? Nadi Ke KinareA? watching sunset and sharing silence.I understand that any normal woman more or less follows the convention. Marring a dream man;raising kids; having her own family unit and her own independent house. Almost half of the life is spent in buying/having our own house. Rearing and raising a child consume much of yours youthful years. By the time your child passes out school, 18 years are gone at the cost of prime years of your life. When we are past 45 we actually come to face with our life and ready to lead and enjoy it with our companion. Does age difference at this stage really matter?

Past is beyond recovery, Future you are never sure of. Even married to a person 3 to 5 years older does not guaranty life long relationship? Life is unpredictable. My hail and healthy wife left me at the age of 43 years all of a sudden completely unexpected. And who knows? Who is going to live longer? A person of 35 years or of 50 years.",,37 to 50,09 Nov 1959,,India,Dharamasala,Athletic,Average,,Brahmin - Saraswat,,Delhi,,Fair ,Fair,Self,B.Sc (Science),"54 yrs, 5ft 9in,

Life is great, a beautiful gift of God. I like to live every moment of my life to the fullest. I am self-motivated, confident, easy going but disciplined man. 
Like to go to Gym regularly and yoga is one of my favorites. So you get the taste of my likings.
I like to read, especially self improving books coz knowledge is an unlimited thing. 
I have great respect for elders. I try to live a balance life between spiritualism and materialistic world. More or less i am happy person and am looking my life partner who can complete my life and i can do hers.
